1 2. The principal of and the interest on any such fund notes shall be payable
2 solely from the housing development fund.
3 3. The fund notes of each issue shall be dated, shall mature at such time or
4 times not exceeding ten (10) years from their date or dates, and may be
5 made redeemable before maturity, at the option of the corporation, at
6 such price or prices and under such terms and conditions as may be
7 determined by the corporation.
8 4. The corporation shall determine the form and manner of execution of
9 the fund notes, including any interest coupons to be attached thereto,
10 and shall fix the denomination or denominations and the place or places
11 of payment of principal and interest, which may be any bank or trust
12 company within or without the state or any agent, including the lender.
13 5. In case any officer whose signature or a facsimile of whose signature
14 shall appear on any fund notes or coupons attached thereto shall cease to
15 be such officer before the delivery thereof, such signature or such
16 facsimile shall nevertheless be valid and sufficient for all purposes the
17 same as if he had remained in office until such delivery.
18 6. The fund notes may be issued in coupon or in registered form, or both,
19 as the corporation may determine, and provision may be made for the
20 registration of any coupon fund notes as to principal alone and also as to
21 both principal and interest, and for the reconversion into coupon fund
22 notes of any fund notes registered as to both principal and interest, and
23 for the interchange of registered and coupon fund notes.
24 7. Any such fund notes shall bear interest at such rate or rates as may be
25 determined by the corporation and may be sold in such manner, either at
26 public or private sale, and for such price as the corporation shall
27 determine to be for the best interest of the corporation and best
