UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 202
1 KRS 198A.030;
2 (b) "Eligibility statement" has the same meaning as in Section 3 of this Act;
3 (c) "Eligible taxpayer" has the same meaning as in Section 3 of this Act;
4 (d) "Federal low-income housing tax credit" has the same meaning as in
5 Section 3 of this Act; and
6 (e) "Qualified low-income housing project" has the same meaning as in 26
7 U.S.C. sec. 42.
8 (2) (a) For taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2027, but before
9 January 1, 2031, there shall be allowed a nonrefundable, transferable
10 affordable housing credit allowed against the tax imposed in KRS 141.020
11 or 141.040 and 141.0401, with the ordering of the credit as provided in
12 Section 5 of this Act.
13 (b) The credit shall be:
14 1. Awarded by the corporation on a project specific basis;
15 2. Subject to the limits in Section 3 of this Act;
16 3. Claimed in the taxable year in which the qualified low-income
17 housing project is placed in service; and
18 4. Available for carryforward for a period not to exceed ten (10)
19 consecutive years, after which any excess credit shall be lost.
20 (3) The affordable housing credit shall not be used in conjunction with any other
21 credit established within this chapter for the construction or substantial
22 rehabilitation of a qualified low-income housing project.
23 (4) If the eligible taxpayer is a pass-through entity, and the credit is not transferred
24 in accordance with subsection (5) of this section, the credit shall be distributed to
25 each partner, member, or shareholder in accordance with that partner's,
26 member's, or shareholder's distributive share for the taxable year in which credit
27 is awarded.
